Task: Initialize Rust project with Cargo workspace and directory structure

Summary: Created the veloterm Rust project from scratch. Set up Cargo.toml with
core dependencies (winit 0.30, wgpu 24, cosmic-text 0.12, log, env_logger,
unicode-width, bytemuck). Established module directory structure following the
spec: src/renderer/ (gpu, glyph_atlas, grid_renderer), src/config/ (theme),
and shaders/ (grid.wgsl). Installed Rust 1.93.0 toolchain.

Files created:
- Cargo.toml (project manifest with dependencies)
- Cargo.lock (locked dependency versions)
- rustfmt.toml (max_width = 100)
- src/main.rs (entry point with env_logger init)
- src/config/mod.rs (config module declaration)
- src/config/theme.rs (theme color placeholder)
- src/renderer/mod.rs (renderer module declarations)
- src/renderer/gpu.rs (GPU pipeline placeholder)
- src/renderer/glyph_atlas.rs (glyph atlas placeholder)
- src/renderer/grid_renderer.rs (grid renderer placeholder)
- shaders/grid.wgsl (shader placeholder)

Why: Establishes the foundational project structure for VeloTerm GPU rendering
pipeline. All subsequent tasks build on this scaffolding.
